	<Title>
		Oophorectomy (ovary removal): A risk factor for dementia?
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Oophorectomy (ovary removal) dramatically lowers estrogen, a hormone that protects your brain.
	</Abstract>
	<Question>
		If I have my ovaries removed before I&apos;m 50, will I be more likely to have dementia when I get older?
	</Question>
